<exercise checkit-seed="0004" checkit-slug="DiffQuotient" checkit-title="Difference Quotient">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Suppose that there is a function <m>g</m> such that <m>g(1) = -2.3</m> and <m>g(0.8) = -2.2</m>. Use these values to estimate <m>g'(1)</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <me>
            g'(1) \approx \frac{ g(0.8) - g(1) }{ (0.8) - (1) } = 
            \frac{ (-2.2) - (-2.3) }{ (0.8) - (1) } = -0.50
        </me>
    </answer>
</exercise>
